deck: Stephen Lindsay is a comic writer and is best known for his Creator Owned content and the hillarious series Jesus Hates Zombies, which can often be found paired with Lincoln Hates Werewolves.
description:
In a press release July 8, 2010 from   Creators Edge Press it was announced that Stephen Lindsay would be taking over as the independent publisher's Marketing Director.  He and his 7-year old son Ayden wrote Warriors of Dharuk in 2011.
 
The press release: 

"Creator’s Edge Press is proud to announce the most recent addition to their partnership in Stephen Lindsay. Stephen is best known for his top-selling book ‘Jesus Hates Zombies’, but also has an array of books currently available online at his personal website www.captionsandballoons.com.  Stephen will take over as Marketing Director for the newly established publishing company, relieving the company’s current Marketing Director Chuck Messinger to focus on his new position as Public Relations Director. “Stephen comes to the group with an understanding and respect for what we want to offer the industry with our line of products. His knowledge of both the industry as well as our marketing agenda makes him an ideal asset for our organization. That and we love the man!” says Chuck Messinger.

“Even before I had the opportunity to meet the Creators Edge team, I knew I liked where the company was headed. They have a real focus on story, and that’s something that is often overlooked within this industry that so easily gets distracted by flashy artists and flavor-of-the-month writers. Story always has been, and always will be, the key. Then, once I did meet the team, I really knew that these were people I wanted to be associated with. I’m extremely excited to join the Creators Edge family I can only hope that my own experience within this industry will help me bring something of value to the table,” says Stephen. Stephen has already brought two of his creator-owned projects to Creator’s Edge Press; Devil’s Trail and Warriors of Dharuk. Devil’s Trail #1 is currently available at comic stores as well as through the company website. Warriors of Dharuk #1 is scheduled for release this Fall.


Creator’s Edge Press is a venue for up-and-coming writers, artists and creative minds. Established and brought to life with a singular vision: keeping independent comics independent.  The company has an extensive repertoire of creator-owned intellectual properties and newly licensed properties with a broad range of genres for all sensibilities.   While the company helps finance and distribute books for creators, they ensure the books remain 100% creator owned.  "
name: Stephen Lindsay

deck: The co-founder of cartoon studio Hanna-Barbera.
description: William Denby "Bill" Hanna (July 14, 1910 - March 22, 2001) was a voice actor, cartoon artist, animator, producer, director, and the co-founder of Hanna-Barbera with Joseph Barbera. Together, the two made some of the most popular cartoons of all time, such as Tom & Jerry, Scooby-Doo, The Flintstones, Huckleberry Hound, Yogi Bear, The Jetsons, and The Smurfs.
name: William Hanna

deck: Rich Ellis the artist of Memorial and a member of Periscope Studio.
description: Rich Ellis is a cartoonist living and working in Portland, Oregon. He earned a bachelors degree in sequential art from the Savannah College of Art and Design. His clients include Marvel Comics, Th3rd World Publishing, Microsoft/MNML, The Oregonian, Comic Foundry, Michael Curry Design, Harper, Walker/Bloomsbury UK, Red 5 Comics, IDW Publishing and the Willamette Week. Rich is a member of Periscope Studio, the largest studio of comic book artists in North America.
name: Rich Ellis
